'''Yoshiki Takaya''' (<U+9AD8><U+5C4B> <U+826F><U+6A39> ''Takaya Yoshiki'', born [[February 21, 1960]]) is a [[mangaka]] best known for creating the [[manga]] ''[[Guyver]]'', which has been adapted into multiple [[anime]] features as well as live action films. ''Guyver'' was serialized in ''[[Sh<U+014D>nen Captain]]'' (published by [[Tokuma Shoten]]) for the lifetime of the magazine from 1985 to 1997. When ''Captain'' was cancelled, the manga moved to ''[[Sh<U+014D>nen Ace]]'', published by [[Kadokawa Shoten]], who also reprinted the collected volumes from the beginning. As of July 2006 there are 24 [[tank<U+014D>bon]] available.

Takaya began however as an [[H manga]] artist under the [[pen name]] '''Morio Chimi''' (<U+3061><U+307F><U+3082><U+308A><U+3092> ''Chimi Moriwo''), with several works printed in the adult manga magazine ''[[Lemon People]]'', published by [[Kubo Shoten]]. The best known of these is ''[[Hades Project Zeorymer]]'', which was adapted as a four episode [[Original Video Animation|OVA]] by [[AIC (company)|AIC]]. He also had stories published in the manga anthology series ''[[Petit Apple Pie]]'' under this pen name. 

